715615f-a.title: Manhattan: 139th Street (West) - 5th Avenue
715615f-a.text:
(1)
West 139th Street, north side, west from the Harlem River, to. S incl.
Fifth Ave., as seen from the Madison Ave. Bridge, and sho ing mainly the
disposal plant of the Department of Sanitation, which occupies the en-
tire block east of Fifth Ave., between 139th and 140th Streets. The
ramp for barge loading does not appear, but would be on the extreme
right.
June 24, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same from a different angle, and showing both the ramp and the
river.
June 24, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
